.TH AXT-BUNDLE 1
.SH NAME
axt-bundle \- emit a session warmup bundle
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B axt-bundle
[\fIROOT\fR]
[\fB--agent\fR|\fB--json\fR]
[\fB--depth\fR \fIN\fR]
[\fB--max-files\fR \fIN\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B axt-bundle
collects a shallow file inventory, local manifest previews, git state, and
next-step hints in one command.
.SH OUTPUT
Human output is used for TTY stdout. Compact text is used when stdout is not a
TTY. JSON output uses schema
.B axt.bundle.v1.
Agent output starts with
.B axt.bundle.summary.v1.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --agent
Emit summary-first JSONL for agents.
.TP
.B --json
Emit the canonical JSON envelope.
.TP
.B --depth \fIN\fR
Limit file inventory depth.
.TP
.B --max-files \fIN\fR
Limit file records in the bundle.
.TP
.B --include-hidden
Include hidden paths.
.TP
.B --no-ignore
Disable ignore-file handling.
